        <!-- icon and title -->
			<div align="left" class="posttitle">
			<span class="posttitle">Re: The Secret World</strong>
			</div>
	<!-- status icon and date -->
			<div align="left" >
			<a class="posttime" name="post527870">
			<span class="posttime">&nbsp;Posted:&nbsp;<strong>07-04-12, 10:48 PM</strong></span>
			
			</div>
	<!-- / status icon and date -->
	<!-- / icon and title -->
    </td>
        <td align="right" valign="middle">
	<!-- controls -->
		
		
		
			<a href="newreply.php?do=newreply&amp;p=527870"><img src="images/buttons/quote.gif" alt="Reply With Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" /></a>		
		
		
		
		
		
		
			
		
        

 

 
 
</div>   
		
		<!-- / controls -->
        </td>
        <td width="30" align="right" valign="middle" nowrap>
			&nbsp;

<a href="showpost.php?p=527870&amp;postcount=106" target="new" rel="nofollow" id="postcount527870" name="106" class="pcount"><strong>#106</strong></a>

			
		</td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_527870"><a href="http://forums.thesecretworld.com/showthread.php?t=34236&amp;highlight=crafting" target="_blank">http://forums.thesecretworld.com/sho...light=crafting</a><br />
<br />
Sticky of game guides. Raithwood's Complete Crafting Guide should have all the patterns you need to remember.<br />
<br />
QL of materials versus toolkit can be semi-confusing. Some of the tool tips are wrong. But basically QL 0 to 1 takes Base Materials. QL 2 to 3 takes Imperfect. Level 4 to 5 takes Normal. Or something like that. The tool tip on the toolkit tells you what level of materials it wants.<br />
<br />
And there's some bugs. I have a Blue QL 3 Glyph toolkit that I can't seem to make anything with; either imperfect or normal quality materials. <br />
<br />
Kind of like I said in my reviews, crafting isn't anywhere near essential. You can use it to get the most out of a particular build you want, swapping out the random properties you've been getting for something more specific. Crafted Greens and Blues will always be stronger than purchased or dropped greens and blues of the same QL. (I think dungeon drops sit at the very top of the food chain.) But it's a difference of only a few points. When you total up all the extra points from every single piece of gear being the highest it can for its QL...it adds up. Right now I have enough metal to make 5 or more QL weapons...but there's really no reason to. I have two good blues from Inferno that can't be beaten. The best I could do is get some blue quality glyphs to put in them. (Which I'm not about to spend Sequins of Solomon Island on.)<br />
<br />
For most people, the gear you get randomly as loot or from missions will be plenty to get you through solo. (It tends to come with a ton of HP on it.) Crafting is just there to take you that little extra distance. I think if dropped gear came with glyphs already on it less frequently, more people might need to craft.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
