    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_527923">As Blood/Chaos, I haven't found that to be true yet. In fact, switching to a pure DPS/Impair build won me fights losing less health than trying to shoehorn in healing or something else into the build. I think my DPS right now is somewhere between 400 - 800 a sec, depending on Crit and pen rates. In the first 10 seconds of a fight, I can strip 30% of a mob's health from it. <br />
<br />
On the flipside, fights requiring AoE are a little trickier. I'm still trying to find the right balance for that. But so far I haven't felt like I'm suffering being pure DPS. (Having about 4500 HP helps too.) I think builds function much better when they're focused. Spreading yourself out over 3 or more activities (Single target DPS, AoE, Healing, Trying to cycle through your passives) results in an ineffective build. Especially when your gear isn't totally on point for what you're trying to do.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
