    <div align="left" id="post_message_527935"><div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="middle">
	
	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Nenjin said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">Spreading yourself out over 3 or more activities (Single target DPS, AoE, Healing, Trying to cycle through your passives) results in an ineffective build. Especially when your gear isn't totally on point for what you're trying to do.</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>Well, you shouldn't be spreading out actives like that, of course. The reason swords is so freaking strong, for example, is that it lets you use lots of passives for self-healing on hit effects. I can't speak much for ranged or chaos, but all the melee and blood, of course, offers self-healing sustain in the passives that let you still kit out your actives for damage.<br />
<br />
I'm running a hammer/fists build right now because the gear swapping is annoying enough that I don't want to **** around too much with saved builds but even with that I can create a kit that triggers a ton of self-heal, damage reduc/mitigation, and damage. I am also very close to making my ONE THOUSAND CUTS build which is just dash attack spamming to troll enemies and friendlies alike.<br />
<br />
But, yea, the combat mechanics are such that most builds are viable to at least some extent but there is always room for optimizing so I shouldn't say that anything is downright bad, I just think for the most optimal soloing you need to hit all your bases somehow.<br />
<br />
Seriously, though, the skill system and combat mechanics in this game are great--just makes me so sad the animations still don't match up (lol at spinning sword ability that has your character just point their sword in the sky instead of, you know, spinning).</div>
