    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_527936">Yeah, the animations and spell effects are the weakest point of combat to me. (Other than the whole thing is formulated to require maximum button presses to reach maximum efficiency.) <br />
<br />
I think if effects looked sexier that most people wouldn't find combat so unpalatable. Because when you finally start acquiring gear with appreciable amounts of stats, all the differences between abilities emerge and you start seeing builds and play styles. None of that is really apparent in the first few hours of Kingsmouth though, where the reported values of abilities being in the same ballpark make it hard to see where the differences are. <br />
<br />
But man, once you start getting the crit and pen rating up.....you suddenly start appreciating HOW you can pump out massive DPS, and all those high-damage, specific use abilities start showing their usefulness.<br />
<br />
In the beginning, Blood Healing seemed so worthless when you're healing per cast less than you're getting hit for. Fast forward about 200 Heal Rating...and suddenly you can heal back to 50 to 75% life and continue fighting.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
