    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_528009">I have to rant a little. Spoilers.<br />
<br />
<div style="margin:5px 20px 20px 20px">

<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>SPOILER:</b>

<input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onclick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != '') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = '';this.innerText = ''; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none'; this.innerText = ''; this.value = 'Show'; }">

</div>

<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">

<div style="display: none;">

So I'm in Egypt and I pick up what looks like your garden variety side quest. It quickly turns out, it's not. After finding a bunch of satellite dishes and downloading the data from them, you get presented with....a bunch of numbers.<br />
<br />
Now, I'm not much of a programmer but I do know a few things. I know what Binary looks like. I know generally that a set of numbers is a numbers system.<br />
<br />
But Base64? Hex? Decimal? How exactly are people who don't know this stuff supposed to figure out what it is? I spent a good hour pumping these sequences into translators, only to find out the values were DOUBLE-ENCRYPTED. When the numbers were parsed and output what at first looked like gibberish to me, I thought I was losing my grasp of basic facts. <br />
<br />
While I really like the investigation missions, they make many assumptions about your knowledge level, life experience and how that relates to solving puzzles. Like, how exactly are you supposed to figure out what a numbers system is just by looking at it? You can't just input the values into Google and have it magically tell you what they are. I spent 20 minutes reading a wiki article to try and get a handle on it...which was automatically screwed up by the fact it was double-encrypted.

</div>

</div>

</div><br />
<br />
I love the missions but goddamn, they make me feel dumb as a post sometimes.</div>
