	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_528074">I did my first instance last night: The Anhk.<br />
<br />
This was an extremely well designed instance. Why? Well, it had 3 things going for it.<br />
<br />
First, almost every encounter taught you something useful for the following encounter. Example: The first thing you fight is a Mote. Next encounter: Numerous motes are used to force movement onto the players while they fight a Boss. Then you encounter some &quot;trash mobs.&quot; During the next boss fight, those trash mobs end up being used as summons. Then you fight a guy who uses an area denial mechanic, which comes up several more times in the instance. Basically, each step teaches you more and more and it is all used in the final encounter.<br />
<br />
Second, There were several excellent boss fights, including a Juggernaut encounter where you have to stay ahead of an advancing boss (unlike the Halls of Reflection, though, you DO have to defeat the advancing boss!) and the aforementioned final encounter. I've never had quite as much fun dying repeatedly...it felt like we were always making progress and not simply beating our heads against a wall of HP.<br />
<br />
Last, visually, the place is pretty cool looking. The bosses are interesting to look at, their FX are fun. Overall, the art worked together to create an interesting play area that provoked a sense of dread.<br />
<br />
I'd give it a 9.5/10 in terms of instance design.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
