    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_528075">I just did several runs of Darkness War last night, once as healer and once as DPS. <br />
<br />
Pretty overgeared for it now that I'm already doing Egypt but...well, as a healer, dungeon instances are very exciting to me. Things can be going fine and then the tank gets whalloped and you spend a minute or so desperately trying to get their HPs back up. It's not like WoW when you fire off your best heal and they go from 10% to 60% right away. Between the damage incoming and the size of your heals, you're slowly building HP back on to the tank, and you're never quite sure if it's going to keep going that way, or if you're tank is about to drop.<br />
<br />
DPS on the other hand....I dunno. Maybe it's all the WoW raiding I've done, but the fights as DPS are almost mind-numbingly easy. &quot;Don't stand in the AoE, kill adds, don't let adds explode on you&quot; is the name of the game in the first three instances that I've done. Maybe it's just the lack of stress compared to healing that makes DPS seem so easy. I guess in truth it's not much easier than WoW as a rogue.<br />
<br />
And of course, there'll be nightmare mode later on, where the real ridiculousness gets turned on. <br />
<br />
Instance design is pretty sweet even though it's linear. I especially liked the Darkness War. Mayan's invading America and doing battle with the native tribes? Sweet. (One of the cutscenes for Darkness War shows you an optional area in the instance where you can earn some extra blue loot if you kill the mobs there.)<br />
<br />
Anyone else tried to change skills in an instance and found one that simply won't work? My Chaos finisher last night would not activate no matter what I did, even though it was reacting properly to how many resources I had, lighting up and greying out when it was supposed to. I had to leave the instance before it worked right.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
